This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in image recognition tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new pooling method with a trainable parameter, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning philosophy and data-driven approach further supports the inclusion of these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and analysis of the proposed method, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and manipulation, which could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
